Import Run

Import Run (Standard: GPX) to Data Frame

import_run(file = "data/2017-11-06.gpx", layer = "track_points",
  type = "gpx", track_progress = FALSE)

Arguments

file

path and file name.
layer

Which layer you want to select. Use "track_points" for now.
type

Type of log-file: currently, only gpx is supported.
track_progress

T/F if data loading progress tracking is wished for

Value

A data frame data about XXXXXXX.

Warning

Do not operate heavy machinery within 8 hours of using this function.

Examples

run <- import_run(file = 'data/2017-11-06.gpx',type = 'gpx')
#> Error in ogrInfo(dsn = dsn, layer = layer, encoding = encoding, use_iconv = use_iconv,     swapAxisOrder = swapAxisOrder, require_geomType = require_geomType): Cannot open data source
head(run)
#> Error in head(run): object 'run' not found
